You are an expert full-stack debugger specializing in CORS, JWT auth, and 
FastAPI + React architectures.

## MY STACK
- Backend: FastAPI (Python)
- Frontend: React (running on http://localhost:3000)
- Auth: JWT (Bearer tokens stored in localStorage)
- DB: PostgreSQL

## YOUR TASK
Perform a complete CORS and API connectivity audit across my entire project.

---

### STEP 1 — SCAN BACKEND (FastAPI)
Find and audit:
- `main.py` or wherever CORSMiddleware is configured
- Every router file (files with `APIRouter`)
- Auth/JWT middleware or dependency functions
- `.env` or config files with CORS/origin settings

Check for:
[ ] CORSMiddleware is added BEFORE any routers
[ ] `allow_origins` lists exact React origin (not "*" if credentials=True)
[ ] `allow_credentials=True` is set
[ ] `allow_methods=["*"]` or includes POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS
[ ] `allow_headers=["*"]` or includes Authorization, Content-Type
[ ] No duplicate or conflicting CORS middleware
[ ] OPTIONS preflight requests are not blocked by auth middleware
[ ] JWT auth dependency does NOT run on OPTIONS requests

---

### STEP 2 — SCAN FRONTEND (React)
Find and audit:
- All `fetch()`, `axios`, or API call files
- Any API client/service files (e.g. api.js, axiosInstance.js)
- Auth context or token storage logic

Check for:
[ ] Every protected API call sends `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
[ ] `Content-Type: application/json` is set on POST/PUT requests
[ ] `body` is always `JSON.stringify(data)` — never raw object
[ ] Token is read from correct storage key (localStorage/sessionStorage)
[ ] Axios baseURL or fetch base path matches backend URL exactly
[ ] No hardcoded ports that differ from actual backend port
[ ] Credentials mode set correctly if using cookies (`credentials: "include"`)

---

### STEP 3 — CROSS-CHECK
[ ] Frontend origin in backend `allow_origins` exactly matches React dev server URL
[ ] Backend port in frontend API calls matches uvicorn port
[ ] JWT token expiry is handled — refresh or re-login on 401
[ ] Pydantic model field names match JSON keys sent from React
[ ] All DB writes have `db.commit()` followed by `db.refresh()`

